# harness/vault.config — OPTIONAL read-only Vault locations (P7). One `<name>=/absolute/path` per line.
#
# The Vault is a sibling knowledge repo (human-curated context/memory), READ-ONLY to the entire Forge by
# convention. This file is OPTIONAL — absent means NO vault (never an error). Paths are ABSOLUTE (a
# relative or '..'-bearing path is out of forge scope and is skipped by harness/vault.sh). The real
# harness/vault.config is gitignored instance data; this .example is the committed template.
#
# SETUP (optional):
#   cp harness/vault.config.example harness/vault.config
#   # then set each vault to its absolute path ON THIS HOST.
#
# The Forge only ever READS the vault for context: `harness/vault.sh paths` resolves the locations and an
# agent Reads the content with its own tools. The vault NEVER drives acceptance, bead state, branch state,
# security policy, or merge authority — the accept-gate is vault-blind, `bd` is the authoritative task
# state, and a human merges. To ADD durable vault content, a human mints a `[VAULT-PROPOSAL]` bead; the
# Forge never writes the vault.
#
# knowledge=/absolute/path/to/my-vault
